500|$|His first release, <b>Roman</b> <b>Candle</b> (1994), {{came about}} when Smith's girlfriend {{at the time}} {{convinced}} him to send a tape of [...] "the most recent eight songs that [...] recorded on borrowed four-tracks and borrowed guitar" [...] to Cavity Search Records. Owner Christopher Cooper immediately requested to release the entire album of songs, which surprised Smith, as he was expecting only a deal for a seven-inch record.|$|E
